{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:24:33.514Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Supervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":" is the primary paradigm in classical machine learning where a model learns from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"labeled examples"},{"type":"text","text":": it receives input features and the corresponding correct answers (labels), and is trained to predict the correct label for new, unseen inputs."}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simple definition:"},{"type":"text","text":" “Think of supervised learning as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"learning by example"},{"type":"text","text":".”"}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core idea: learning from features + labels"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In supervised learning, you need "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"two components"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Features"},{"type":"text","text":" – the input data provided to the model (e.g., date, email text, image pixels)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Labels"},{"type":"text","text":" – the correct answers you want the model to learn to produce (e.g., temperature, “spam/not spam”, object class)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The model:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Makes predictions using only the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"features"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Its performance is evaluated by comparing its predictions to the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"true labels"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"objective (cost) function"},{"type":"text","text":" measures how wrong it is, and the model is adjusted to reduce that error"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"After training"},{"type":"text","text":", the model only needs features to make predictions; it no longer needs labels."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Supervised learning in classical ML vs. Generative AI"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Supervised learning = Classical Machine Learning (mostly)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In classical machine learning, supervised learning is the dominant approach for:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Classification"},{"type":"text","text":" (predicting a category):"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Spam detection: “spam” vs “not spam” - Fraud detection: “fraud” vs “not fraud” - Disease diagnosis: “diseased” vs “healthy”\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Regression"},{"type":"text","text":" (predicting a number): - Predicting temperature, price, sales, etc. - Example: predict temperature on Jan 31 given the date as a feature"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Classic supervised ML algorithms include:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Linear regression"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Logistic regression"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Support Vector Machines (SVM)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Nearest-neighbor methods"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tree-based algorithms (Decision Trees, Random Forests, Gradient Boosting)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"These are all "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"discriminative models"},{"type":"text","text":": they learn decision boundaries between classes or a mapping from features to labels."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generative AI uses different paradigms"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generative AI typically "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"does not"},{"type":"text","text":" rely on standard supervised learning with explicit labels per example. Instead, it uses:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Self-supervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., LLMs):"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- The model predicts the next token in a sequence from the rest of the text - Labels are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"derived from the data itself"},{"type":"text","text":", not manually provided\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unsupervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., GANs, diffusion models): - The model learns the data distribution without explicit labels\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reinforcement learning"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., RLHF for LLMs): - The model is optimized based on feedback from human preferences or reward signals"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key conceptual difference:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Supervised (classical ML)"},{"type":"text","text":": learns "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"P(\\text{label} \\mid \\text{input})"}},{"type":"text","text":" – “Given this input, what’s the label?”"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generative AI"},{"type":"text","text":": learns "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"P(\\text{data})"}},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"P(\\text{data}, \\text{label})"}},{"type":"text","text":" – “What does all the data look like?” and then samples new examples"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Classical ML"},{"type":"text","text":" is mostly "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"supervised discriminative"},{"type":"text","text":" (predict labels)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generative AI"},{"type":"text","text":" is mostly "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"self-supervised/unsupervised generative"},{"type":"text","text":" (create new data)"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Supervised vs. Unsupervised (core difference)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The article explicitly states:"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"“The only difference between supervised and unsupervised learning is how the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"objective function"},{"type":"text","text":" works.”"}]}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Supervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- You know the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"correct answer"},{"type":"text","text":" for each training example - The objective function compares the model’s prediction to the true label - Used for problems where there is a clear answer (classification, regression)"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unsupervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- You "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"do not know"},{"type":"text","text":" the correct answer; there may be no single “right” answer - The objective function judges the model’s estimate based on how good/plausible it is (e.g., “does this image look realistic?”) - Used for clustering, dimensionality reduction, and some generative tasks"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Supervised learning"},{"type":"text","text":" is classical ML where the model learns from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"features + labels"},{"type":"text","text":" to predict the correct answer for new inputs."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It’s primarily used for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"classification"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"regression"},{"type":"text","text":" in classical ML (spam detection, fraud detection, forecasting)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generative AI"},{"type":"text","text":" mostly uses "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"self-supervised"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"unsupervised"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reinforcement learning"},{"type":"text","text":", not standard supervised learning with explicit labels."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The core difference between supervised and unsupervised is how the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"objective function"},{"type":"text","text":" uses (or doesn use) labels during training."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Supervised learning is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"discriminative"},{"type":"text","text":" (learns boundaries), while generative AI is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"generative"},{"type":"text","text":" (learns the full data distribution)."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
